--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 With this plan in mind, he waited as Vexomza grew into more and more bold rebellion, for he must get her off her guard and await an appropriate opportunity.<br>
<br>
She took to frequenting the 'Foreign Quarter', expressing boredom with the torture of victims and other proper entertainments in the upper class regions of Neriak. Carefully, so as not to warn his prey, he arranged to keep her under seamless surveillance.<br>
<br>
The legendary patience of Bitierzal the Torturer was rewarded, when Vexomza began staying out through sleep periods, and was seen speaking with members of the lower races. Ahhh, he thought, so it will be a romance! He had his spies seek out an appropriate male of the lower races.<br>
<br>
Bitierzal the Torturer had exquisite taste, able to choose just the right implement for each phase of the long twisting of a soul. This one, he judged, calls for a 'true believer.'<br>
<br>
Soon enough, he intercepted correspondance from a pathetic devotee of a healer god, apparantly thinking to investigate and thwart the ultimate death, the permanent one. This one will do, he thought.<br>
<br>
This self styled, 'holy mage' will follow the weakness of light eagerly to his doom, and once Vexomza's heart is bound securly to him, it will be well and truly twisted in the loss.<br>
<br>
Bitierzal the Torturer had a forged response sent to this human's correspondence indicating that the secret he sought resided in Neriak. Which in truth it did.<br>
<br>
Adept in the art of deception, he did nothing overt as far as Vexomza was concerned. Bitierzal the Torturer arranged for the guards and others to turn a blind eye to the human, allowing him to come and go freely as long as he did not penetrate deeper then the Foreign Quarter.<br>
<br>
Yet Bitierzal the Torturer knew that being young, Vexomza could be easily influenced, in shallow ways. He contrived to be overheard by her when discussing the relative prowess of some of the lower races, specifically that some humans have been not completely incompetent in some of the lesser magical arts.<br>
<br>
He was not disapointed to learn in time that his daughter seemed infatuated with the human magician, though she was not completely flagrant, having adopted the alias of 'Iris'. <br>
<br>
This was apparantly inspired by an insipid romantic ballad performed in a particularly shabby establishment in the Foreign Quarter. To help pass the time as his plan came into fruition, he had the bard abducted and tortured to death over the course of the next month. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubitierzalthetorturer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bitierzal the Torturer</A> at: 2/13/02 6:49:07 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10>A Bard for a Day</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  